{
  "stem": "26142.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Boeinghart ?] that produced great scientists, leaders, and also-- and also poets.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The poet Avigdor Hameiri, he changed his name from-- Firestone was his name.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He changed it to Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Hameiri was one of the students in this here-- in this famous Yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Also-- also, a Zionist leader by the name of Dr.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Josef Potter-- he was also a student at that Yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And that my very oldest brother, Eliezer also was a student at that Yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I know, an uncle of mine-- my mother's younger brother-- his name was Svee and mother's name Drimmer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He was also a student in that Yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But he left the Yeshiva, and acquired a secular education.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He changed his name from Drimmer to Darvas, and his first name from Svee, which was Herman, to Armin.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And he became, later, a high school teacher.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And that's-- we'll talk about him later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I was hiding out in his place later.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My level of education was to-- to go to-- we went to-- to cheder, of course, and finished the public school, which was 8-- 8 grades.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One year-- one year the Hebrew school was not able to exist, because they didn't have enough money.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I went one year to a Ukrainian school-- Russian.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I learned Cyril-- the Cyril language-- and later on, went to Czech school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There wasn't enough students, because the Czech-- [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Czechs only had-- they'd send in administrative people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They-- they-- the majority of the people were Ukrainians.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They called them small Russians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And about a little bit better than 10% were the Jewish-- the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So when I finished that public school, and I became a bar mitzvah, I wanted to go to a high school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But this-- there was no high school around.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
